headline: Meta Clashes With Apple, Google Over Age Check Legislation
summary: (Bloomberg) -- The biggest tech companies are warring over who’s responsible for children’s safety online, with billions of dollars in fines on the line as states rapidly pass conflicting laws requiring companies to verify users’ ages.Most Read from BloombergTrump Awards $1.26 Billion Contract to Build Biggest Immigrant Detention Center in USThe High Costs of Trump’s ‘Big Beautiful’ New Car Loan DeductionCan This Bridge Ease the Troubled US-Canadian Relationship?Salt Lake City Turns Winter Olymp
